const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is my LG refrigerator compressor covered under warranty?",
    a: "Following the Rosen v. LG Electronics class action settlement, LG extended its Inverter Linear Compressor warranty to 10 years (parts and labor) for models manufactured between 2014 and 2022. Covered model series include LFXS, LFXC, LMXS, LMXC, LRMVS, LRMVC, LSXS, LSXC, LTCS, and LRTLS. We verify coverage on every LG compressor call before quoting anything. If your unit is covered, you pay diagnostic and labor only — not compressor parts. Call us with your model number and purchase date and we'll check coverage on the spot."
  },
  {
    q: "What does the clicking sound from my LG refrigerator mean?",
    a: "A rhythmic clicking or click-buzz sound from the back of your LG refrigerator — typically every 2-3 seconds — is the compressor attempting to start and failing. This is the classic LG linear compressor failure signature, known as error code 67 (compressor lock). Before diagnosing a compressor failure, we check the start relay first — a rattling relay is a $25 fix that can mimic compressor failure. If the relay is solid and windings test correctly, the internal compressor mechanism has failed. This is exactly the situation where warranty coverage applies."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my LG washer show an OE error?",
    a: "OE on an LG washer means the drain cycle didn't complete. The most common cause by far is a clogged drain pump filter — LG front-load washers have a filter behind a small access panel at the lower front of the machine that needs quarterly cleaning. Most homeowners don't know it exists until the OE error appears. We clear the filter, check the drain pump impeller, and show you the maintenance procedure before we leave. In most OE cases, no parts are needed."
  },
  {
    q: "What is the LG d80 or d90 error on my dryer?",
    a: "d80, d90, and d95 are vent blockage warnings — they indicate 80%, 90%, or 95% airflow restriction. These are not component failures; they're telling you the dryer vent needs cleaning. If you see these codes, the vent run from the dryer to the exterior needs to be cleared. We inspect and clear dryer vents on every LG dryer call in Southern California. A restricted vent that causes the dryer to overheat will eventually damage the heating element and thermal fuse."
  },
  {
    q: "Is the LG Direct Drive motor warrantied?",
    a: "LG warranties the Direct Drive motor on washers for 10 years on parts. If your LG washer drum is not spinning and the motor has failed, warranty coverage may apply depending on your model and purchase date. We verify motor warranty coverage the same way we check compressor coverage — before quoting, not after."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does LG appliance repair cost in Southern California?",
    a: "Our diagnostic fee is $89, credited toward the repair. Common LG repairs: drain pump filter cleaning $89 (service fee only, no parts), door latch replacement $120-180, heating element $150-230, ice maker assembly $180-280, compressor replacement $350-550 out of warranty (or parts-only cost in-warranty). We give a written estimate before any work begins."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you use genuine LG OEM parts?",
    a: "Yes. All repairs use genuine LG OEM parts. Using non-LG parts on a unit still under warranty voids the remaining coverage — we never do this. Every repair comes with a 90-day warranty on parts and labor."
  },
];

const schemaJSON = JSON.stringify({
